## 3. Network Access Control (NACL) - Logical Rule Reference
*While NACLs are not JSON files, the configuration logic used for the public subnet is documented here:*

| Rule # | Type | Protocol | Port Range | Source | Allow/Deny |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| 100 | SSH | TCP | 22 | [Admin-IP]/32 | ALLOW |
| 200 | HTTP | TCP | 80 | 0.0.0.0/0 | ALLOW |
| 300 | ICMP | ALL | ALL | 0.0.0.0/0 | ALLOW |
| * | ALL Traffic | ALL | ALL | 0.0.0.0/0 | **DENY** |

